Vale SA (VALE5)  is studying doubling the
output capacity of its Moatize coal project in  Mozambique ,
newspaper  Valor Economico   reported , citing Galib Chaim, head of
the company in the African country.  The board of the Rio de Janeiro-based company may approve
shortly doubling the projectâ€™s production capacity to 22 million
metric tons per year, the newspaper said. Vale is considering
additional investments in Mozambique, including coal, phosphate
and nickel projects, Sao Paulo-based Valor said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
